!begin_node (!kw [no_toc_subsubsubnodes])
!html_name cmd_no_toc_subsubsubnodes

Do not output paragraphs in tables of contents.

!begin_xlist [(!TYPEPOSITION)]

!item [(!TYPEPOSITION)] (!SWITCH), (!PREAMBLE)

!item [(!SYNTAX)] (!T)!/no_toc_subsubsubnodes [(!FORMAT)](!t)

!item [(!DESCRIPTION)]
If you use this switch inside the preamble UDO will print only the
chapter titles, section titles and subsection titles inside the table
of contents.

Another possibily is to use the switch (!KW [depth]) with
the (!KW [toc]) command.

!item [(!EXAMPLE)]
(!T)!/no_toc_subsubsubnodes [win,stg,html](!t)

!item [(!EXISTSSINCE)] Release~5 Patchlevel~8

!item [(!SEEALSO)]
(!KW [tableofcontents]), (!KW [toc]), (!KW [depth]), (!link [Tables of contents] [Tables of contents])

!end_xlist

!end_node
